name: Nana Yōkai Collection: Kappa
description: Nana Yōkai Collection is a series of illustrations, created with the aim of sharing traditional Japanese mythology. In this series, Nana will be personifying herself as different Yōkai (Japanese spirits). The first one is Kappa. Kappa live in rivers. They love eating cucumbers and sumo wrestling. They have a plate on their head full of water; if the water dries up, the Kappa gets weak and could die.
